SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 426
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor Susan Long, 2025 Professional Award
recipient of the John J. Duncan Sr. Award for
Senior Advocacy.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such individual is Susan Long of Knoxville, who was recently named
the 2025 Professional Award recipient of the John J. Duncan Sr. Award for Senior Advocacy;
and
WHEREAS, the John J. Duncan Sr. Award for Senior Advocacy was created to honor
those who steadfastly work to improve the lives of seniors in the Knoxville community, as the
award's namesake did throughout his career; recipients are professionals and community
members who have been nominated in recognition of their tireless efforts on behalf of seniors;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Long earned her undergraduate degree in marketing and completed
master's degree coursework in advertising at the University of Tennessee, after which she
began her professional journey in teaching and real estate; however, it was in 1985 that she
found her true calling—serving older adults; and
WHEREAS, she began this chapter of her professional life as an administrator at the
Commonwealth Senior Living facility, where her leadership quickly made an impact, leading to
full occupancy within three years; and
